					<description><![CDATA[Trying to get tech to work can seem like getting a three year old to clean up his room.&#160; Yet, tech doesn’t have the advantage of being loved, which makes it all the more frustrating when we can’t get it to do what we want.&#160;<a class="read-more" href="https://llgt.cafe/finding-love-in-the-right-places">&#8230;</a>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>Trying to get tech to work can seem like getting a three year old to clean up his room.&nbsp; Yet, tech doesn’t have the advantage of being loved, which makes it all the more frustrating when we can’t get it to do what we want. &nbsp;</p>



<p>I don’t know about you, but my frustrations range from phones that mysteriously turn on, open an app and begin doing whatever it pleases.&nbsp; Usually, I can tell that my phone is on because it warms up in my pocket.&nbsp; By the time I notice it, however, the batter has drained half its power.</p>



<p>Software can be another problem. While Adobe offers some of the best software, it can also be some of the most frustrating.&nbsp; Presently, I’m trying to get my computer connected to the internet, but its being very trying. &nbsp;</p>



<p>Love is so important; it should be included in the list of things that we need in order to survive.&nbsp; Like water, air and shelter, love might just be key to survival.&nbsp; And though it may not be necessary for every individual, it is for the survival of the human race. &nbsp;</p>



<p>Yes, we can survive without love, but we cannot thrive without it.&nbsp; And though we can just survive, the better option is to thrive. &nbsp;</p>



<p>Can we find love if and when we are alone?&nbsp; I think so.&nbsp; Why, you may ask? &nbsp; Or, how?&nbsp; It’s simple.&nbsp; If you can find someone else who needs love and, if you are willing to be open and vulnerable, you can find love. &nbsp;</p>



<p>First Corinthians 13 reminds us that, if we don’t have love, our actions, our very lives are useless.&nbsp; For the Bible tells us that God, Himself, is love.&nbsp; We love because He first loved us. &nbsp;</p>



<p>If love is so important, how do we find it?&nbsp; First, search for God.&nbsp; You can “ask Him into your heart.”&nbsp; It’s kind of like giving God your heart.&nbsp; God already owns everything.&nbsp; We just have to surrender our will to His. &nbsp;</p>



<p>Second, we can decide to meet others where they are.&nbsp; Activity look to help others, meeting then where they are and not where we wish they were.&nbsp; God met us where we were when He sent Jesus to die on a cross.&nbsp; We meet Him when we accept His gift.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
